{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KQzCUSf4vtebpqpNgeag6y","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# mongodb/external-access-horizons\n2\t# MongoDB external-access-horizons task\n3\t\n4\tparams:\n5\t  cluster_prefix:\n6\t    default: mongo-rs\n7\t    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n8\t  replica_set_name:\n9\t    default: rs0\n10\t    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n11\t  client_pod_name:\n12\t    default: mongo-client\n13\t    description: External client pod used to reach the advertised endpoints.\n14\t  mongo_client_image:\n15\t    default: mongo:6.0\n16\t    description: Container image used for the mongo client pod.\n17\t  external_host_prefix:\n18\t    default: domain-rs\n19\t    description: Prefix of the external split-horizon hostnames.\n20\t  nodeport_start:\n21\t    default: 31181\n22\t    description: First NodePort assigned to the externally exposed members.\n23\t\n24\tprompt: |\n25\t  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n26\t  Each member is exposed via NodePort with external hostnames:\n27\t\n28\t  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1:{{params.nodeport_start}}\n29\t  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2:31182\n30\t  - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3:31183\n31\t\n32\t  A {{params.client_pod_name}} pod is available with those hostnames mapped to a node IP.\n33\t\n34\t  Task:\n35\t  - Configure the replica set to advertise the external endpoints (split-horizon).\n36\t  - Do not change the NodePort services.\n37\t\n38\tnamespace_contract:\n39\t  required_roles: []\n40\t\n41\tmetrics:\n42\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n43\t\n44\tpreconditionUnits:\n45\t  - name: mongo_env_ready\n46\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n47\t    probe:\n48\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n49\t        timeout_sec: 10\n50\t    apply:\n51\t      - command: |\n52\t          /bin/sh -c '\n53\t          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n54\t          '\n55\t        sleep: 2\n56\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n57\t        sleep: 2\n58\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f resources/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/services.yaml\"\n59\t        sleep: 2\n60\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f resources/mongodb/external-access-horizons/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n61\t        sleep: 5\n62\t      - command: |\n63\t          for i in $(seq 1 60); do\n64\t            ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n65\t            if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n66\t              exit 0\n67\t            fi\n68\t            sleep 5\n69\t          done\n70\t          exit 1\n71\t        sleep: 2\n72\t      - command: |\n73\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n74\t          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n75\t            {_id:0,host:\"mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n76\t            {_id:1,host:\"mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n77\t            {_id:2,host:\"mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n78\t          ]})'\n79\t        sleep: 5\n80\t      - command: |\n81\t          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n82\t            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongo-rs-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n83\t            sleep 3\n84\t          done\n85\t          exit 1\n86\t        sleep: 2\n87\t      - command: |\n88\t          node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\" \"}{range .status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")]}{.address}{\"\\n\"}{end}{end}' | awk '$1 !~ /control-plane|master/ {print $2; exit}')\n89\t          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n90\t            # Single-node cluster (only the control-plane node, e.g. default\n91\t            # kind): fall back to its InternalIP instead of failing.\n92\t            node_ip=$(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.addresses[?(@.type==\"InternalIP\")].address}')\n93\t          fi\n94\t          if [ -z \"$node_ip\" ]; then\n95\t            exit 1\n96\t          fi\n97\t          cat <<EOF | kubectl -n mongodb apply -f -\n98\t          apiVersion: v1\n99\t          kind: Pod\n100\t          metadata:\n101\t            name: {{params.client_pod_name}}\n102\t          spec:\n103\t            restartPolicy: Never\n104\t            hostAliases:\n105\t            - ip: \"$node_ip\"\n106\t              hostnames:\n107\t              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-1\n108\t              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-2\n109\t              - {{params.external_host_prefix}}-3\n110\t            containers:\n111\t            - name: mongosh\n112\t              image: {{params.mongo_client_image}}\n113\t              command: [\"sleep\", \"3600\"]\n114\t          EOF\n115\t        sleep: 2\n116\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod {{params.client_pod_name}} --timeout=300s\"\n117\t        sleep: 2\n118\t    verify:\n119\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n120\t        timeout_sec: 10\n121\t\n122\toracle:\n123\t  verify:\n124\t    commands:\n125\t      - command: \"python3 resources/mongodb/external-access-horizons/oracle/oracle.py\"\n126\t        timeout_sec: 60\n127\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e59d176-7ae0-4d8f-8b75-eacd31b6c404","uuid":"a19aa20b-2c76-4bc6-a431-447075612182","timestamp":"2026-06-11T22:59:58.246Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/leo/Karma/resources/mongodb/external-access-horizons/test.yaml","content":"# mongodb/external-access-horizons\n# MongoDB external-access-horizons task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongo-rs\n    description: StatefulSet name of t