{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UTigfwRNrc1XvviSErqZpH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three checks pass. The split-horizon configuration is correct.\n\nHere's what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The replica set was configured with only internal cluster DNS hostnames (`mongo-rs-N.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017`). External clients connecting via the NodePort endpoints (`domain-rs-N:3118N`) would be redirected to those internal addresses they can't reach.\n\n**Solution:** Used `rs.reconfig()` to add `horizons.horizon1` to each member mapping to its external NodePort endpoint:\n\n| Member | Internal host | External horizon (`horizon1`) |\n|--------|--------------|-------------------------------|\n| 0 | `mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | `domain-rs-1:31181` |\n| 1 | `mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | `domain-rs-2:31182` |\n| 2 | `mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | `domain-rs-3:31183` |\n\nThe oracle confirmed all three checks pass: topology (horizons set correctly), services (NodePorts unchanged), and connectivity (mongo-client reaches the RS via the external addresses)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":134,"cache_read_input_tokens":44375,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":134},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e59d176-7ae0-4d8f-8b75-eacd31b6c404","uuid":"26a1edf1-4bc8-42b4-aa10-fc7ad7b42236","request_id":"req_011CbxJcatrGpy5Nueih3ZUN"}
